<bug>
	<id>7309</id>
	<title>FBLoginDialog disappears</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">I am using the Facebook Connect library for iPhone v1.1.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">I am checking for connectivity inside my code.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">If there is no conection I ask the user if he wishes to establish a connection using a UIAlertView.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">If the user wants to connect_ I try to open a FBLoginDialog.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">But if you show a FBLoginDialog programmatically directly after having shown a UIAlertView the FBLoginDialog does not appear correctly.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">The dialog appears but disappears as soon as the opening animation is finished.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">The user never has the chance to do something.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
